sources.homepage:
Vimalkumar Jeyakumar

Department of Computer Science
444 GATES
353 Serra Mall
Stanford University
Stanford, CA 94305

I am a second year Ph.D. student in the Department of Computer Science at Stanford University. Before this, I was at Indian Institute of Technology Madras where I graduated in 2009, with a B.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering. My old website from IIT Madras days might still have something useful.

I am broadly interested in Computer Networks and Secure Systems. I am also fascinated by visualisation and love solving problems. With my new Canon EOS Rebel T1i and a couple of lenses, I am also trying out photography with help from my friend Vaibhav, who frequently goes on trips to scenic places.

Here are some shots:

  • Russian Ridge, California (Spring; Mar 2010)
  • Trip to Big Sur, California (Jan 2010)
  • Some of my good shots of 2009 (Nov 2009--1st week of 2010)
  • Few panoramas
  • Pictures of cooking! (Dec 2009--May 2010)

If you find this colour scheme familiar, I borrowed it from Prof. Don Knuth's website.

Publications

  • Novel SAT-based Peak Dynamic Power Estimation for Digital Circuits;
    Shyamala K, Vimalkumar J, and Kamakoti V;
    JOLPE Vol. 5 No. 4 December 2009.

Courses

  • CS244: Advanced Topics in Networking (Winter 2010)
  • CS240: Advanced Topics in Operating Systems (Spring 2010)
  • CS155: Computer and Network Security (Spring 2010; audit)
  • CS241: Secure Web Programming (Spring 2010; audit)
My room-mate Ananth Raghunathan.
